      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "In commit \"node: Use mempool from node context instead of global\" (fa963d3818afea82061615b9939361444e5b5c2d)\r\n\r\nI think you can get rid of this code now that the test framework is managing `g_rpc_node`:\r\n\r\n```diff\r\n--- a/src/test/rpc_tests.cpp\r\n+++ b/src/test/rpc_tests.cpp\r\n@@ -112,15 +112,10 @@ BOOST_AUTO_TEST_CASE(rpc_rawsign)\r\n     std::string notsigned = r.get_str();\r\n     std::string privkey1 = \"\\\"KzsXybp9jX64P5ekX1KUxRQ79Jht9uzW7LorgwE65i5rWACL6LQe\\\"\";\r\n     std::string privkey2 = \"\\\"Kyhdf5LuKTRx4ge69ybABsiUAWjVRK4XGxAKk2FQLp2HjGMy87Z4\\\"\";\r\n-    NodeContext node;\r\n-    node.chain = interfaces::MakeChain(node);\r\n-    node.mempool = std::move(m_node.mempool);\r\n-    g_rpc_node = &node;\r\n     r = CallRPC(std::string(\"signrawtransactionwithkey \")+notsigned+\" [] \"+prevout);\r\n     BOOST_CHECK(find_value(r.get_obj(), \"complete\").get_bool() == false);\r\n     r = CallRPC(std::string(\"signrawtransactionwithkey \")+notsigned+\" [\"+privkey1+\",\"+privkey2+\"] \"+prevout);\r\n     BOOST_CHECK(find_value(r.get_obj(), \"complete\").get_bool() == true);\r\n-    g_rpc_node = nullptr;\r\n }\r\n```\r\n\r\nSeems to work",
      "commit_id" : "fa7c5017a9056b33e230d78f7ff6879e3d8941a5",
